title: 820-2936 Intermittant Fan Spin
message:
I have an 820-2936 with Intermittant Fan Spin (no Liquid Damage)

PP3V42 - 3.47V
PPBUS_G3H -12.58 V
PP5V_S5 - 5.0 V
PP3V3_S5 - 3.3V
PP5V_S3 - 5V then off, 5V then off
PP3V3_S3 - 3.3V then off, 3.3V then off

I tried new clock chip, same result.  Any ideas?

Thanks

title: 820-2936 Intermittant Fan Spin
message: CPU Vcore coming on? Liquid damage?

title: 820-2936 Intermittant Fan Spin
message:
No liquid damage.

No CPU VCore

PP5V_S0 and PP1V05_SO are at 5V and 1.05V respectively, but also intermittant  (about 250ms on and 3 sec off)

title: 820-2936 Intermittant Fan Spin
message:
ALL_SYS_PWRGD tries to appear?
Can you catch at least a pulse in that 250ms?

title: 820-2936 Intermittant Fan Spin
message: Yes, ALL_SYS_PWRGD is 3.2V for 320ms, pulse shows very clean on scope.

title: 820-2936 Intermittant Fan Spin
message: So no voltage pulses at L7510? Check R7402 for corrosion. I doubt this "just" happened, what is the history?
